Argentine Stocks: Ledesma, Mirgor, Petrobras, Tenaris Decrease

-- B y   B r y a n   G i b e l
-- 
2011-08-18T16:12:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-18/argentine-stocks-ledesma-mirgor-petrobras-tenaris-decrease.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 11:23 a.m.  New York  time.  The Merval Index fell 4 percent to 2,875.53, as all 19
stocks in the gauge tumbled.  Ledesma SAAI (LEDE AF), the Argentine sugar producer, fell
5.2 percent to 7.30 pesos. Raw sugar for October delivery
declined 0.71 cent, or 1.4 percent, to 29.07 cents a pound on
ICE Futures U.S. in New York.  Mirgor SACIFIA (MIRG AF), the Argentine builder of climate-
control systems for automobiles, dropped 5.6 percent to 100.50
pesos. Morgan Stanley cut its forecast for global growth this
year, citing an “insufficient” policy response to  Europe ’s
sovereign debt crisis, weakened confidence and the prospect of
fiscal tightening. Mirgor’s major customers include Fiat SpA,
Volkswagen AG, Daimler AG, Renault SA and Chrysler Group LLC.  Petroleo Brasileiro SA (PETR4)  , the oil and gas producer,
fell 5.4 percent to 59.50 pesos as crude prices dropped. Oil
futures for September delivery declined 5 percent to $83.22 a
barrel on the  New York Mercantile Exchange .  Tenaris SA (TEN)  ,
the world’s largest producer of steel tubes used in the
 petroleum industry , dropped 5.3 percent to 71.20 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Bryan Gibel in New York at 
 bgibel@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
